4.1 Minor mode
==============

‚ÄėUniline‚Äô is a minor mode.  Activate it temporarily:

   ‚ÄėM-x uniline-mode‚Äô

   Exit it with:

   ‚ÄėC-c C-c‚Äô

   The current major mode is still active underneath ‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô.

   While in ‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô, overwriting is active, as well as long lines
truncation.  Also, a hollow cursor is provided (customizable).  Those
settings are reset to their previous state when exiting ‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô.


