5 The ‚Äė<insert>‚Äô key
********************

The ‚Äė<insert>‚Äô key is a prefix for other keys:
   ‚ÄĘ for drawing arrows, squares, crosses, o-shapes glyphs,
   ‚ÄĘ for handling rectangles,
   ‚ÄĘ for inserting ‚Äė# = - +‚Äô which otherwise change the brush style,
   ‚ÄĘ for trying a choice of mono-spaced fonts.

   Why ‚Äė<insert>‚Äô?  Because:
   ‚ÄĘ ‚ÄėUniline‚Äô tries to leave their original meaning to as many keys as
     possible,
   ‚ÄĘ the standard meaning of ‚Äė<insert>‚Äô is to toggle the
     ‚Äėoverwrite-mode‚Äô; but ‚ÄėUniline‚Äô is already in ‚Äėoverwrite-mode‚Äô, and
     de-activating overwrite would break ‚ÄėUniline‚Äô.

   So preempting ‚Äė<insert>‚Äô does not sacrifice anything.

   *Customization*

   Another key may be defined instead of ‚Äė<insert>‚Äô.  Type:

     M-x customize-variable uniline-key-insert


