7.2 Filling a rectangle
=======================

While the rectangular mode is active, press ‚Äėi‚Äô to fill the rectangle.
You will be asked to choose a character.  You have those options:

   ‚ÄĘ for a regular character like ‚Äėt‚Äô, just type it.
   ‚ÄĘ ‚ÄėSPC‚Äô or ‚ÄėDEL‚Äô for a shade of grey ‚Äė" ‚ĖĎ‚Ėí‚Ėď‚Ėą"‚Äô among the 5 available
     in UNICODE.  ‚ÄėSPC‚Äô to make it darker and darker.  ‚ÄėDEL‚Äô to make the
     rectangle lighter and lighter.
   ‚ÄĘ ‚ÄėC-y‚Äô to chose the first character in the top of the kill ring.

   The above selection is the same as for the flood-fill action (see
*note Flood-fill::).


