7.3 Moving a rectangular region
===============================

Select a region, then press ‚Äė<insert>‚Äô.

   Use arrow keys to move the rectangle around.  A numeric prefix may be
used to move the rectangle that many characters.
   ‚ÄĘ Under ‚ÄėHydra‚Äô, be sure to specify the numeric prefix with just
     digits, without the ‚ÄėAlt‚Äô key.  Typing ‚Äė15 <left>‚Äô moves the
     rectangle 15 characters to the left.  ‚ÄėM-15 <left>‚Äô does not work.
   ‚ÄĘ Under ‚ÄėTransient‚Äô, use the ‚ÄėAlt‚Äô key, like anywhere else in
     ‚ÄėEmacs‚Äô.  Type ‚ÄėM-15 <left>‚Äô to move the selected rectangle 15
     characters to the left.

   Press ‚Äėq‚Äô, ‚Äė<return>‚Äô, or ‚ÄėC-g‚Äô to stop moving the rectangle.

   The ‚ÄėC-_‚Äô key may also be used to undo the previous movements, even
though the selection is still active.



