11 Hydra or Transient?
**********************

The basic usage of ‚ÄėUniline‚Äô should be easy: just move the point, and
lines are traced.  Change brush to draw thicker lines.

   More complex actions are summoned by the ‚Äė<insert>‚Äô key, with or
without selection.  This is a single key to remember.  Then a textual
menu is displayed, giving the possible keys continuations and their
meaning.  All that is achieved by the ‚ÄėHydra‚Äô or ‚ÄėTransient‚Äô libraries,
which are now part of ‚ÄėEmacs‚Äô (thanks!).

   The ‚ÄėHydra‚Äô and ‚ÄėTransient‚Äô libraries offer similar features.  Some
users may prefer one or the other.

   ‚ÄėUniline‚Äô was developed from day one with ‚ÄėHydra‚Äô.  ‚ÄėTransient‚Äô is a
late addition.

