11.2 Instantly selecting Hydra or Transient
===========================================

It is now possible to switch user interfaces on the fly.

   To do so, look at the "Customize" entry in the Uniline menu.  This
menu is available:
   ‚ÄĘ from the menu-bar at the top of the Emacs screen (if not made
     invisible),
   ‚ÄĘ by left-clicking on ‚Äė"Uniline"‚Äô in the mode-line, at the bottom of
     the Emacs screen.

   Note that the changes are for the current session only.  To
permanently choose Hydra or Transient, change your
=~/.emacs=initialization file as describe in *note Selecting Hydra or
Transient::.

   The actions performed by the menu are:
   ‚ÄĘ ‚Äė(load-library "uniline-hydra")‚Äô
   ‚ÄĘ ‚Äė(load-library "uniline-transient")‚Äô

   You can execute them directly or by other means.


