13.1 Language environment
=========================

The so called "language environment" in Emacs can cause unwanted line
breaks, like in this drawing:




     ‚ē∂‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚Ē¨‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ēģ
                            ‚Ēā           ‚Ēā
                            ‚Ēā           ‚Ēā
                            ‚Ēā           ‚Ēā
                            ‚ēį‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ēĮ
        unexpected broken lines

     ‚ē∂‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚Ē¨‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ēģ
           ‚Ēā           ‚Ēā
           ‚Ēā           ‚Ēā
           ‚Ēā           ‚Ēā
           ‚ēį‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ‚ēĮ
        expected continuous lines


   The above example was drawn first with the ‚ÄėChinese-BIG5‚Äô language
environment, then with the ‚ÄėEnglish‚Äô environment.

   There is nothing specific about ‚ÄėChinese-BIG5‚Äô.  It is just an
instance picked out from more than 100 language environments.

     C-x RET l Chinese-BIG5
     C-x RET l English

   In ‚ÄėChinese-BIG5‚Äô, some characters are considered twice as wide as
standard characters.  Whereas in ‚ÄėEnglish‚Äô, all characters needed by
Uniline are 1 unit wide.

   Thanks to *rumengling* (GitHub) for discovering and diagnosing the
issue!

   To workaround the issue, when entering ‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô, the width of
all characters Uniline uses is checked.  If some of them are more than
1, the ‚Äėchar-width-table‚Äô variable is patched.

   What are the consequences of this patch?  The ‚Äėchar-width-table‚Äô
variable is an Emacs global.  Therefore the patch by Uniline will affect
all buffers.  As the characters touched by the patch are graphic, and
have nothing to do with Chinese, it should not have any significance on
text written in Chinese.

   It was pondered whether Uniline should put back ‚Äėchar-width-table‚Äô at
its original value upon exiting ‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô, or leaving the patch.
For now, it has been decided to leave it.  Because anyway, intertwining
several ‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô and changes to the language environment is
intractable.

   In case of something, re-setting the language environment to its same
value cancels the patch to ‚Äėchar-width-table‚Äô by Uniline.


