13.2 Compatibility with Picture-mode
====================================

‚ÄėPicture-mode‚Äô and ‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô are compatible.  Their features
overlap somehow:
   ‚ÄĘ Both implement an unlimited buffer in east and south directions.
   ‚ÄĘ Both visually truncate long lines (actual text is not truncated).
   ‚ÄĘ Both set the overwrite mode (‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô activates
     ‚Äėoverwrite-mode‚Äô, while ‚Äėpicture-mode‚Äô re-implements it)
   ‚ÄĘ Both are able to draw rectangles (‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô in UNICODE,
     ‚Äėpicture-mode‚Äô in ASCII), copy and yank them.

   They also have features unique to each:
   ‚ÄĘ ‚ÄėPicture-mode‚Äô writes in 8 possible directions
   ‚ÄĘ ‚ÄėPicture-mode‚Äô handles TAB stops
   ‚ÄĘ ‚ÄėUniline-mode‚Äô draws lines and arrows


File: uniline.info,  Node: Compatibility with Artist-mode,  Next: Compatibility with Whitespace-mode,  Prev: Compatibility with Picture-mode,  Up: How Uniline behaves with its environment?

13.3 Compatibility with Artist-mode
===================================

‚ÄėArtist-mode‚Äô and ‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô are mostly incompatible.  This is
because ‚Äėartist-mode‚Äô preempts the arrow keys, which give access to a
large part of ‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô features.

   However, it is possible to use both one after the other.


