15 Mouse support
****************

The out-of-the-box mouse support of ‚ÄėEmacs‚Äô works perfectly.  Except
when the mouse clicks on a position outside the buffer.  This happens
when clicking past the end of a too short line, or past the end of the
buffer.

   To handle those cases, a few standard ‚ÄėEmacs‚Äô functions have been
extended to add blank characters or blank lines.  Doing so, the
mouse-click now falls on a valid part of the buffer.  Of course, those
extensions are only active on ‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô activated buffers.

   Beware that when the window is at the same time zoomed with ‚ÄėC-x C-+
C--‚Äô AND horizontally scrolled with ‚ÄėC-x <‚Äô, the cursor positioning is
not accurate.  This is due to ‚ÄėEmacs‚Äô limitations and bugs.  Just click
twice to fix the inaccuracy.


