16.1 use-package, the straightforward way
=========================================

The ‚Äėuse-package‚Äô library became the de-facto standard to manage
packages in your ‚Äė.emacs‚Äô initialization file.  The ‚Äėuse-package‚Äô
library comes along with Emacs.  It can (among other services) delay
loading external packages until they are used, and bind keyboard
shortcuts to the package‚Äôs entry points.

   Add the following lines to your ‚Äė.emacs‚Äô file, and reload it, if not
already done.  This says that the popular Melpa repository is one of the
central store of third parties packages.  To day, it provides almost
7000 packages to choose from.

     (add-to-list 'package-archives
                  '("melpa" . "http://melpa.org/packages/")
                  t)
     (package-initialize)

   Alternately you may customize this variable:

     M-x customize-variable package-archives

   Then add those lines in your Emacs initialization file (usually
‚Äė~/.emacs‚Äô):

     (use-package uniline-hydra
       :bind ("C-<insert>" . uniline-mode))

   or:

     (use-package uniline-transient
       :bind ("C-<insert>" . uniline-mode))

   This tell Emacs:
   ‚ÄĘ Be prepared to load ‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô when the user request it, but do
     not load it now.
   ‚ÄĘ Bind the ‚ÄėC-<insert>‚Äô keys to the function ‚Äėuniline-mode‚Äô.  This
     shortens the longer ‚ÄėM-x uniline-mode‚Äô command.  Any other key
     combinations can be bound, as you prefer.  ‚Äė<insert>‚Äô happens to
     also be the key used inside ‚ÄėUniline‚Äô (customizable).
   ‚ÄĘ Load either the ‚Äėuniline-hydra‚Äô or the ‚Äėuniline-transient‚Äô file, as
     you prefer.  This gives Uniline one or the other flavour of
     user-interface.

   There is an alias to ‚Äėuniline-hydra‚Äô:

     (use-package uniline
       :bind ("C-<insert>" . uniline-mode))

   If you are using *note straight.el:: with ‚Äėuse-package‚Äô, and have
‚Äė(setq straight-use-package-by-default t)‚Äô, you have the following
options:

     ;; uniline-hydra using the alias
     (use-package uniline)

     ;;; uniline-hydra explicitly requested
     (use-package uniline-hydra
       :straight uniline)

     ;;; install and load uniline-transient
     (use-package uniline-transient
       :straight uniline)


